`Break` the `for loop` when you get the first occurrence of the  `char` you are searching. Your current code will currently return the last index of the char.

    if(str.charAt(index) == replacedFirst)
    {
      indexFirst = index;
      break;
    }

As an alternative, you can also do an enhanced `for` loop with `String.toCharArray()` to iterate on each `char`:   

    public static void main(String[] args) {
	      String str = &quot;she is so nice&quot;;
	      char replacedFirst = &#39;e&#39;;
	      int indexFirst = 0;

	      for (char c : str.toCharArray()) {
		      if(c == replacedFirst)
		      {
		    	  break;
		      }
		      indexFirst++;
	      }
	      System.out.println(indexFirst);
	}

This will use your `indexFirst` and increment it each iteration, and `break` if the `char` matches.	

